================================================================================
NOTES ON .gitignore FILE:
================================================================================

1. Prevents sensitive files and build artifacts from being committed to Git
2. node_modules/ - Never commit dependencies (npm install recreates them)
3. dist/ - Build output directory (generated by npm run build)
4. .env files - Contains sensitive configuration and API keys
5. Editor files - Personal IDE settings should not be shared
6. Log files - Runtime logs should not be committed


================================================================================
ADDITIONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (Optional)
================================================================================

If you need to add more environment variables in the future:

# Feature Flags
VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=false
VITE_ENABLE_DEBUG_MODE=false

# External Services
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_key_here
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn

# Build Configuration
VITE_BUILD_VERSION=1.0.0
VITE_BUILD_DATE=2026-01-17

Remember: Always prefix with "VITE_" for Vite to expose them to your app!


================================================================================
USAGE IN CODE:
================================================================================

To access environment variables in your React components:

import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL
import.meta.env.VITE_SOCKET_URL
import.meta.env.VITE_APP_NAME
import.meta.env.VITE_APP_VERSION

Example:
const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL || 'http://localhost:5000/api';


================================================================================
PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
================================================================================

For production, create a .env.production file:

VITE_API_URL=https://api.taskbuddy.com/api
VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://api.taskbuddy.com
VITE_APP_NAME=TaskBuddy
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0

Then build with:
npm run build

This will use the production environment variables.


